identifier: The Minneapolis Assessor's Office tracks property data to assist in classification and valuation of real property. This data is regularly updated to accurately reflect market conditions. Below are descriptions of the attributes.PIN - The 13 digit property identification number that uniquely identifies a parcel of land.AssessmentYear - the year for which the data is relevant, typically one year later than the calendar year. For example, data collected in 2016 is relevant to the 2017 assessment year.Plat - The identification number of the plat of land that the land parcel is in.Address - The street address of the parcel.ZipCode - The postal code of the parcel.PropertyType - The classification assigned by Assessor staff to the property.SizeInSqFt - The size of the land parcel.X - The X coordinate of the property in the NAD 83 HARN Hennepin County projection (WKID: 103734)Y - The Y coordinate of the property in the NAD 83 HARN Hennepin County projection (WKID: 103374)Neighborhood - The name of the Minneapolis neighborhood that the parcel is in.Community - The name of the Minneapolis community that the parcel is in.Ward - The Minneapolis Ward number that the parcel is in.Zoning - The zoning code of the parcel.LandUse - The land use of the parcel.LandValue - The assessed value of the land on the property, excluding and building or improvements.BldgValue - The total assessed value of any structures or buildings on the property.TotalValue - The total assessed value of the property.ExemptStatus - Shows whether the parcel is tax exempt or not.Homestead - Shows whether the parcel is homesteaded or not.
